definition_en: A class of stainless steels characterized by a face-centered cubic crystal structure (austenite) at room temperature, known for their high corrosion resistance and ductility.
definition_ko: 상온에서 면심 입방 결정 구조(오스테나이트)를 특징으로 하는 스테인리스강의 한 종류로, 높은 내식성과 연성을 가진다.

slots.context_ko: Effects of LWR Coolant Environments on Fatigue Design Curves of Austenitic Stainless Steels
